messages.message: regarding the `local-crafting-aihub.json` file. I am getting a cypress error when pointing at this cause it’s a JSON file (`ENVIRONMENT=local-crafting-aihub  yarn  e2e:open`). When I use a `.js` file it works fine. Is this JSON file to be used in a different way?
The JS file isn’t in git ignore, which I’m happy to add. But was wondering if I’m just doing it wrong.

it seems like this may have to do w/ @CJ recent updates (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/58478). These used to be jsons but are now `js` files. Perhaps because the json is git ignored it wasn’t included in the change
got it. Ok I’ll update the gitignore
